Active Architecture Initiative: In Implementation (Issue #429)
GPU Inference / Workflow Execution Decoupling
Currently, GPU VMs run the entire job (18–27 min) even though actual GPU inference takes only 2–4 min (3–16% of job time). The remaining 80%+ is Gemini API calls and CPU work, GPU sits idle but the slot stays locked. This caps throughput at ~64 concurrent jobs under GCP's L4 quota.

The fix: Move workflow execution to Cloud Run Jobs (CPU-only, auto-scaling). GPU VMs become a shared inference-only pool, called via HTTP only during the brief GPU phases. A local proxy inside each Workflow Runner resolves GPU URLs just-in-time, no changes required to bp-workflow-engine. Expected result: 5–30× throughput improvement on the same GPU quota.

Current status: Approved and in active implementation on branch feat/gpu-decouple. System is transitional, both the current co-located path and the new decoupled path exist simultaneously.

Audit impact: Deployments, monitoring, and rollback procedures currently must account for both architecture states. 
